ing & reboot to hardware troubleshooting Maintain order and cleanliness in a data center environment and common areas Escalating issues to senior technicians and management as needed/required Travel between sites/locations when required Required Skills Honest, highly motivated, dependable and able to work with minimal supervision Work in a fast paced 24x7 environment with flexibility to work after-hours and weekends when needed Basic understanding of computer hardware and components \u2013 GPU, Ram, CPU, Motherboard, etc. Work well with others across multiple remote teams Basic understanding and use of Windows & Linux/Unix Operating systems Learn new concepts quickly Researching solutions to troubleshoot hardware and network issues as needed Passionate about learning new software, troubleshooting and developing comprehensive distributed systems Possess excellent communication skills and self confidence Perform duties constantly and without deviations unless otherwise instructed Have strong attention to detail, maintain high quality standards Reliability to be on time and available when expected Creative while working within the boundaries of policies, procedures & guidelines Valid driver's license and your own vehicle Able to pass a Drug and Alcohol Screening & Criminal Background check Preferred Skills Knowledge of blockchain technologies, systems, and hardware such as ASIC Mining hardware is preferred. Excellent understanding of network infrastructure, protocol, and services. Experience in data center environment Understanding electrical and mechanical systems used in a data center environment, including Transformers, Generators, Switchgear, PDU units, HVAC???????????? Functional knowledge of programming and scripting languages. Experience with ticketing systems Associate's degree in IT-related field plus two years of progressively responsible experience preferred. Ubiquiti/Cisco network infrastructure experience Experience with installation and troubleshooting of electrical wiring and electrical circuits Physical Requirements for the Data Center Operations Walk job sites in uneven terrain. Regularly lift and/or move up to 50 pounds; and participate in group lifts for 50 pounds or more. Work shifts longer than eight hours in duration. Work in noisy areas with much hotter and colder temperatures than standard office environmental conditions Perform physical tasks all day without becoming overly tired, such as Coordinate body movements when using tools or equipment. Reach and stretch to position equipment and fixtures while maintaining balance. Occasional bending or twisting of the body to work in tight and/or narrow spaces Use hands to manipulate small wires and objects. Apply muscular force quickly to objects and equipment. Push or pull heavy objects into position. Experience: IT Technician Credentials Preferred High School Diploma Electrical certifications a plus Analytical troubleshooting Ability to follow specific policies and procedures Excellent written and verbal communication skills NOTE: This job description is not intended to be all-inclusive. Employee may perform other related duties as negotiated to meet the ongoing needs of the organization. EZ Blockchain is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Qualified applicants will be considered without regard to age, race, color, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, disability, or veteran status. Job Type: Full-time Pay: $13.00 - $15.00 per hour Experience: Data Center: 1 year (Preferred) Education: High school or equivalent (Required) Location: Tennyson, IN 47637 (Required) Working Days: Monday (Required) Tuesday (Required) Wednesday (Required) Thursday (Required) Friday (Required) Schedule: Weekends required 8 hour shift Monday to Friday On call Company's website: www.ezblockchain.net Work Remotely: No ", 
